OL,3,CLiam Payne: Hotel guest describes
OL,4,Cseeing him minutes before his death
OL,6,FWhen asked what was going through his
OL,7,Fmind at this point, Watson responded:
OL,8,F"It didn't seem real. You almost had
OL,9,Fto pinch yourself to understand and
OL,10,Fprocess what you were seeing, but it
OL,11,Fjust was an out-of-body experience,
OL,12,Fsurreal."
OL,14,FWatson said he "had a suspicion" it
OL,15,Fwas Payne almost immediately, "just
OL,16,Fbased on the state of mind and the
OL,17,Fcondition he was in earlier...that was
OL,18,Fmy first thought."
